quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
40,17,"(It will then be said): “Today shall everyone be fully recompensed for his deeds. None shall be wronged today. {1} Surely Allah is Swift in Reckoning.” {2}",footnotes:1:That is
40,18,"(O Prophet), then warn them of the Day that has drawn near, {1} the Day when hearts full of suppressed grief will leap up to the throats and the wrong-doers shall neither have any sincere friend {2} nor intercessor whose word will be heeded. {3}",footnotes:1:The word hameem as used in the original implies such a friend of a person as is aroused to action when he sees him being beaten
40,19,"He knows even the most stealthy glance of the eyes and all the secrets that hearts conceal."
40,20,"Allah will judge with justice, whereas those whom they call upon beside Him cannot judge at all. Surely Allah � and He alone � is All- Hearing, All-Seeing. {1}",footnotes:1:That is
40,21,"Have they not journeyed in the land that they might observe the end of those who came before them? They were even greater in strength than they and left behind more splendid traces in the land. Then Allah seized them because of their sins and they had none who could protect them from Allah."
40,22,"They came to this end because their Messengers would come to them with Clear Signs {1} and yet they would refuse to believe. So Allah seized them. He is indeed Strong, Terrible in Retribution.",footnotes:1:Bayyinat means three things:
40,23,"Verily We sent Moses {1} with Our Signs and a clear authority {2}",footnotes:1:For the other details of the story of the Prophet Moses (peace be upon him)
40,24,"to Pharaoh and Haman {1} and Korah. They said: “(He is) a sorcerer, an utter liar.” {2}",footnotes:1:“A manifest authority”: With such clear signs as left no doubt that he had been sent by Allah
40,25,"When Moses brought them the Truth from Us they said: “Kill the sons of all the believers who have joined him, but spare the women.” {1} The guile of the unbelievers always ends in vain. {2}",footnotes:1:As already mentioned in (Surah Al-Aaraf
